      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Printing from movable type eliminated the scribe but could not immediately replace the illuminator — early printed books left spaces for hand-drawn initial capitals, a transitional practice that persisted for decades before decorative woodcut initials took their place. The drop cap survived this transition intact, carrying the manuscript tradition forward into the age of mechanical reproduction. Printing from movable type eliminated the scribe but could not immediately replace the illuminator — early printed books left spaces for hand-drawn initial capitals, a transitional practice that persisted for decades before decorative woodcut initials took their place. The drop cap survived this transition intact, carrying the manuscript tradition forward into the age of mechanical reproduction. Printing from movable type eliminated the scribe but could not immediately replace the illuminator.",
